1 (a) “Baton” means a cylindrical instrument that is designed to
2 deliver a blunt force contact or a strike to a person in close
3 proximity.
4 (b) “Chemical agent” means any chemical which can rapidly
5 produce sensory irritation or disabling physical effects in humans,
6 which disappear within a short time following termination of
7 exposure. The term includes, without limitation, items commonly
8 referred to as tear gas, pepper spray, pepper balls and oleoresin
9 capsicum.
10 (c) “Electronic stun device” means a device that:
11 (1) Emits an electrical charge or current that is transmitted
12 by projectile, physical contact or other means; and
13 (2) Is designed to disable a person or animal temporarily or
14 permanently.
15 (d) “School police officer” means a peace officer who:
16 (1) Is employed by the board of trustees of a school district;
17 or
18 (2) Provides services to a charter school pursuant to a
19 contract entered into with the board of trustees of a school district
20 pursuant to NRS 388A.384.
21 Sec. 2. (Deleted by amendment.)
22 Sec. 3. (Deleted by amendment.)
23 Sec. 4. (Deleted by amendment.)
24 Sec. 5. (Deleted by amendment.)
25 Sec. 5.5. The first report required pursuant to section 1 of this
26 act:
27 1. Is due on or before the first day of the 2026-2027 school
28 year; and
29 2. Must contain the information required pursuant to section 1
30 of this act for the 2025-2026 school year.
31 Sec. 6. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025.
